column2: description

Featuring a leather belt and platinum buttons, this lavender jumpsuit is designed for fun, self-expression and self-confidence. This outfit can exist not only in the virtual world, but also in your wardrobe. Just look, friends, at these cute hearts on the chest! Just wonderful!
I created this jacket with the use of materials similar to liquid magma inspired by the power of volcano phenomenon.
The mystical and the natural. The spiritual is in the mundane and natural.

My brand Porka_X reflects my vision of future clothes. Creating virtual clothes - I create more than clothing, I create a character. I see it as a canvas, where I'm trying to find the best shape and then apply prints on it. Print - is my self-expression. My prints reflect my passion, what is in my mind. The first impression people usually get from clothes, gestures, moves. Working in CLO3D I have an opportunity to create my own installations. Characters, that will present clothes how I see them. When I work with virtual clothes I feel freedom and pass this feeling to others. Virtual life, like virtual clothes, help us to get rid of prejudice

"Somewhere, in a sparsely populated galaxy, there is a planet like any other. The creatures of this world have four limbs. The two lower limbs enable them to move forward and backward, and the two upper limbs enable them to kill"

This quote is from experimental sci-fi animation masterpiece called ‘Fantastic Planet’ directed by Rène Laloux and based on Stefan's Wul novel. It isn't hard to guess whom this quote is referring to as 'the creatures' with four 'limbs'. It's also easy to understand that Syro 'Drague' Knit is a loving tribute to this very movie. This magnificent blue garment has a loose cropped fit and it is topped with a 3D visualization of the main character inhabiting "Fantastic Planet", called "Drague" as the sweater does.

The meaning of the 'Drague' Knit is based on film's narrative allegory about animal rights and human rights, as well as racism — problems that remain extremely relevant to this day.

Darkness 2.0 is a sleeveless halterneck jumpsuit. Taking the classic men's shirt and suit as the prototype, through 3D three-dimensional tailoring, the original structure was dismantled and rebuilt into Darkness 2.0. The shirt is disassembled into two symmetrical parts, which are added to the sides of the jumpsuit as the outer skirt. The front waist has an outer apron with a classic suit hem structure, and a fishtail-shaped hem design.

This uniform is inspired by Aura which is displayed as a gradient repelling and attracting different energy layers and colours.  
The whole look gives a feeling of dreaminess and mystery.

A lot of my designs are focused on bringing the digital and the natural together. In this case I my starting point was in the ethereal beauty of the shadows of plants in the wind. I found it fascinating how it contrasts with the way we view digital images, where we are able to see digital images through the light our screens emit, we can see these projections of plants by the absence of that light. The garments themselves are transparent in a purposefully artificial way to let the natural but digitised light shine from withing them.

The dress is inspired by the shining stars of the night sky
In the center of the composition, a bright star, from it softly fa down the drapery and closes behind a smaller star.
The accent of the dress is a translucent hem strewn with star pollen. Wave-like shiny threads of the pattern convey the movements of the clouds. In this way, this composition looks vicious from all sides.
Futuristic contemporary Block Chain dress reflects a connection between physical and digital worlds.  Block Chain dress consists of the mirror mini dress and removable chain skirt.
